The U.S. Federal Reserve Bank, the European Central Bank and the British, Swiss and Canadian central banks have decided to fight the financial market crisis together.
More than a hundred billion dollars will be placed on the currency markets through auctions.
It will be for banks to sell, through an auction system, the interest rates at which they are ready to borrow money.
As an example, the U.S. Fed will auction $40 billion and, in addition, will supply $24 billion to the European and Swiss central banks.
